{"title": "Selective Historical Armoury", "content": "Military fiction set in the past, World War II in particular, will often inexplicably leave out weapons that should be very common, often in favour of \"cooler\" but rarer or even anachronistic items. In films, this can be explained by availability of props, but video games have little excuse other than the developers cutting corners, especially if they took the time to model other weapons that have little in-game use, like pistols.\n\nThe opposite of Rare Guns: In these cases, it is weapons that should be abundant in the setting that are conspicuous by their absence. Compare with Anachronism Stew, Videogame Historical Revisionism, Improperly Placed Firearms and Weapons Kitchen Sink.", "url": "https://tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/SelectiveHistoricalArmoury", "media_links": ["/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Film/Flyboys", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Film/PainAndGain", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Literature/TheGunsOfTheSouth", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/VideoGame/CallOfDuty", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/VideoGame/CallOfDuty2", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/VideoGame/CallOfDutyWorldAtWar", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/VideoGame/ModernWarfare", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/VideoGame/Battlefield", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/VideoGame/ForgottenHope", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/VideoGame/MedalOfHonor", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/VideoGame/MedalOfHonorPacificAssault", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/VideoGame/MedalOfHonorRisingSun", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/VideoGame/MedalOfHonorVanguard", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/VideoGame/MedalOfHonorAirborne", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/VideoGame/DayOfInfamy", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/VideoGame/Commandos", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/VideoGame/HiddenAndDangerous", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/VideoGame/CloseCombat", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/VideoGame/SteelPanthers", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/VideoGame/PanzerGeneral", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/VideoGame/BattlefieldBadCompany", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/VideoGame/FarCry2", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/VideoGame/CallOfDuty", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/VideoGame/ModernWarfare", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/VideoGame/Cal